Los Berros first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Los Berros had a population of 623. The population density was {{convert|247.9|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Los Berros was 441 (70.8%) [[White Americans|White]], 7 (1.1%) [[African Americans|African American]], 3 (0.5%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 16 (2.6%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 44 (7.1%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 112 (18.0%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 141 persons (22.6%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Los Berros CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0644042 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 28, 2025}}</ref>

The census reported that 614 people (98.6% of the population) lived in households, 9 (1.4%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and no one was institutionalized.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 217 households, out of which 61 (28.1%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 153 (70.5%) were married-couple households, 3 (1.4%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 31 (14.3%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 30 (13.8%) had a male householder with no partner present. 35 households (16.1%) were one person, and 20 (9.2%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.83.<ref name=DP1/> There were 178 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (82.0% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Los Berros CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0644042 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 28, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 125 people (20.1%) under the age of 18, 64 people (10.3%) aged 18 to 24, 131 people (21.0%) aged 25 to 44, 168 people (27.0%) aged 45 to 64, and 135 people (21.7%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 44.5{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 105.6 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 235 housing units at an average density of {{convert|93.5|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 217 (92.3%) were occupied. Of these, 161 (74.2%) were owner-occupied, and 56 (25.8%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

